{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:sirach.24",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "sirach",
    "chapterNumber": 24,
    "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24",
    "summary": "Source text for Sirach 24 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:1",
      "text": "Wisdom will praise her own soul, and will proclaim her glory in the midst of her people.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:2",
      "text": "She will open her mouth in the congregation of the Most High, and proclaim her glory in the presence of his power.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:3",
      "text": "“I came out of the mouth of the Most High, and covered the earth as a mist.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:4",
      "text": "I lived in high places, and my throne is in the pillar of the cloud.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:5",
      "text": "Alone I surrounded the circuit of heaven, and walked in the depth of the abyss.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:6",
      "text": "In the waves of the sea, and in all the earth, and in every people and nation, I obtained a possession.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:7",
      "text": "With all these I sought rest. In whose inheritance shall I lodge?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:8",
      "text": "Then the Creator of all things gave me a command. He who created me made my tent to rest, and said, ‘Let your dwelling be in Jacob, and your inheritance in Israel.’",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:9",
      "text": "He created me from the beginning, before the ages. For all ages, I will not cease to exist.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:10",
      "text": "In the holy tabernacle, I ministered before him. So I was established in Zion.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:11",
      "text": "In the beloved city, likewise he gave me rest. In Jerusalem was my domain.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:12",
      "text": "I took root in a people that was honored, even in the portion of the Lord’s own inheritance.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:13",
      "text": "I was exalted like a cedar in Lebanon, And like a cypress tree on the mountains of Hermon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:14",
      "text": "I was exalted like a palm tree on the sea shore, like rose bushes in Jericho, and like a fair olive tree in the plain. I was exalted like a plane tree.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:15",
      "text": "Like cinnamon and aspalathus, I have given a scent to perfumes. Like choice myrrh, I spread abroad a pleasant fragrance, like galbanum, onycha, stacte, and as the smell of frankincense in the tabernacle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:16",
      "text": "Like the terebinth, I stretched out my branches. My branches are glorious and graceful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:17",
      "text": "Like the vine, I put forth grace. My flowers are the fruit of glory and riches.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:19",
      "text": "“Come to me, all you who desire me, and be filled with my fruits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:20",
      "text": "For my memory is sweeter than honey, and my inheritance than the honeycomb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:21",
      "text": "Those who eat me will be hungry for more. Those who drink me will be thirsty for more.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:22",
      "text": "He who obeys me will not be ashamed. Those who work with me will not sin.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:23",
      "text": "All these things are the book of the covenant of the Most High God, the law which Moses commanded us for an inheritance for the assemblies of Jacob.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:25",
      "text": "It is he who makes wisdom abundant, as Pishon, and as Tigris in the days of first fruits.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:26",
      "text": "He makes understanding full as the Euphrates, and as the Jordan in the days of harvest,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:27",
      "text": "who makes instruction shine forth as the light, as Gihon in the days of vintage.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:28",
      "text": "The first man didn’t know her perfectly. In like manner, the last has not explored her.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:29",
      "text": "For her thoughts are filled from the sea, and her counsels from the great deep.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:30",
      "text": "I came out as a canal stream from a river, and as an irrigation ditch into a garden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:31",
      "text": "I said, “I will water my garden, and will drench my garden bed.” Behold, my stream became a river, and my river became a sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:32",
      "text": "I will yet bring instruction to light as the morning, and will make these things clear from far away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:33",
      "text": "I will continue to pour out teaching like prophecy, and leave it to all generations.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:sirach.24.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "sirach",
      "chapterNumber": 24,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Sirach 24:34",
      "text": "See that I have not labored for myself only, but for all those who diligently seek wisdom.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
